    <section id="device-info" class="bg-body  py-24">
        
            <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-2xl grid-cols-1 items-center gap-x-8 gap-y-16 px-4 py-24 sm:px-6 sm:py-32 lg:max-w-7xl lg:grid-cols-2 lg:px-8">
              <div>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-200 sm:text-4xl scroll-animation">HydroMatic Device</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-gray-200 scroll-animation">Description: We develop a device that utilizes sensors to monitor and supply oxygen in hydroponic setup. It ensures optimal growing conditions and facitlitates oxygen delivery to aerate water for growth efficiency.</p>
          
                <dl class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-6 gap-y-10 sm:grid-cols-2 sm:gap-y-16 lg:gap-x-8">
                  <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-4">
                    <dt class="font-medium text-gray-200 scroll-animation">1. Water Level Sensor</dt>
                    <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-200 scroll-animation">Description: A device that measures the level of water in a container, providing real-time data for applications.</dd>
                  </div>
                  <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-4">
                    <dt class="font-medium text-gray-200 scroll-animation">2. DS18B20 Temperature Sensor</dt>
                    <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-200 scroll-animation">Description: A digital temperature sensor capable of measuring temperatures ranging from -55°C to +125°C.</dd>
                  </div>
                  <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-4">
                    <dt class="font-medium text-gray-200 scroll-animation">3. Air Pump</dt>
                    <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-200 scroll-animation">Description: An electric or manual device that moves air from one location to another, typically used to aerate water in hydroponic system, ensuring oxygen for plant roots.</dd>
                  </div>
                  <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-4">
                    <dt class="font-medium text-gray-200 scroll-animation">4.ESP8266 NodeMCU v1.0 (ESP-12E)</dt>
                    <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-200 scroll-animation">Description: A low-cost Wi-Fi microchip with full TCP/IP stack and microcontroller capabilities, often used in IoT projects for wireless connectivity and control of devices.</dd>
                  </div>
                  <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-4">
                    <dt class="font-medium text-gray-200 scroll-animation">5. NodeMCU Baseboard</dt>
                    <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-200 scroll-animation">Description: A development board designed for the ESP8266, providing easy access to GPIO pins, power supply, and programming interfaces, facilitating rapid prototyping of IoT applications.</dd>
                  </div>
                  <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-4">
                    <dt class="font-medium text-gray-200 scroll-animation">6.Relay Module</dt>
                    <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-200 scroll-animation">Description: An electronic component that allows a low-power signal to control a high-power circuit, it is used to control the Air Pump.</dd>
                  </div>
                </dl>
              </div>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-2 grid-rows-2 gap-4 sm:gap-6 lg:gap-8 scroll-animation">
